+## ADR-0059 — Directional significance for triage: build D1 as a triage-local Sender relationship resolver (no self-entity); pull P3/P4a ahead of the suppression slice
+
+**Decision.** Un-defer ADR-0050 **D1** (personal-relevance significance) and build it as the fix for triage's **failure A** — cold inbound (e.g. a LinkedIn "give me a recommendation") classified `awaiting_reply` and minting a "reply to X" todo regardless of who the sender is or who the user is to them. Significance is **per-relationship and directional** ("who am I *to this sender*"), **not** a global declared self-role. The **significance score stays a scalar** (ADR-0057 unchanged); a new **triage-local `Sender relationship` resolver** composes that scalar with the sender's `entities` row + the user's identity `user_facts` + a shared-org-domain test to derive `{relationType, direction, theirDesignation, yourRole}`, which feeds the todo rubric. **No self-entity** is minted in v1. Graph population is **passive-capture only** (never cold-start), split into a now-buildable backfill (**P4a**) and a deferred onboarding seed (**P4b**). Build detail in [docs/plans/long-term-memory-v1.md](./docs/plans/long-term-memory-v1.md).
+
+**Why this is its own ADR.** Surfaced 2026-06-15 from a prod complaint; it reverses a deliberate prior stance (16b's "judge the stake from the email ALONE", ADR-0050/0051 amendment 2026-06-09), un-defers a parked primitive (D1), reorders a plan locked the day before, and evolves the [ADR-0050 amendment 2026-06-10] division-of-labor ruling (seniority = LLM judgment via the rubric) into a **computed graph signal** consumed deterministically. Each is hard-to-reverse or surprising-without-context.
+
+**Micro-decisions.**
+
+1. **Build it right, no interim rubric hack.** An intrinsic-only rubric is *structurally* incapable of the directional call (a valuable stranger and a low-obligation-to-me senior person tie on every email-alone signal). Patching the rubric again would whack-a-mole against principles-over-exemplars. The fix is the missing signal, not more clauses.
+
+2. **Directional, not a global self-role.** "Who am I to this sender" is relationship-relative; a single global "I'm a CEO" knob can't express that a recommendation-seeker is noise to a founder but may matter to a job-seeker. Direction is **derived per-sender**.
+
+3. **No self-entity in v1.** The resolver needs the user's org/role (already in `user_facts`: `company`/`job_title`) and the sender's (their `entities.metadata`) + a shared-org-domain test (sender domain ∈ the user's account domains — already a term in the significance blend). None of that needs a self **node**. A self-entity only earns its place to *store* explicit typed `user→contact` edges (`reports_to`/`manager_of`); derived direction covers v1 and keeps `user_facts` the single source of truth for who the user is (kills the duplication/identity-sync risk). Trade-off: "your role" is free-text, so seniority comparison is model-judged, not a clean enum — acceptable at single-user scale.
+
+4. **Significance score stays scalar; the edge lives where it's consumed.** Of the four ADR-0057 consumers (enrichment gate · triage sender priority · meeting-prep · todo D1), only **todo D1** needs the directional bundle. Baking the edge into the shared score would tax three consumers for one and contradict the "blend → one scalar" framing. The `Sender relationship` resolver is a **triage-module function** that *reads* the scalar and composes the edge — the four-consumer contract does not move (no ADR-0057 amendment).
+
+5. **Rubric rewrite — consume, don't infer; category stays honest.** 16b flips from "judge the stake from the email ALONE — you do not have the user's relationships" to "judge stake from the email **plus the provided `Sender relationship` block**; never infer a relationship beyond what's given." When the graph is empty (most senders mid-rollout) the resolver returns `stranger/no-data` → 16b **degrades to exactly today's intrinsic-only behavior** (additive, safe by construction). The hardcoded **founder/CEO/CTO LinkedIn carve-out in 16a is deleted** (title-proxy replaced by real significance). The gate sits on the **todo promotion**; `awaiting_reply` **stays the honest category** (a cold ask *is* a direct unanswered question) — consistent with the ADR-0058-slice "orthogonal check, NOT a category bend" principle. A low-significance cold ask is tagged Awaiting, mints no todo, and sinks within the bucket via the existing `triage sender priority` consumer. Backed by the ADR-0055 eval lane (cold recommendation-seeker → no todo; significant person's ask → todo).
+
+6. **Population is passive-capture only — never cold-start.** Cold-start (v2) is **account-holder-scoped** and has **no correspondence history to read at callback time** (the `documents` store is empty + new users default to `gated`); it must not mint contact `entities`. Entity/`entity_relations` population is ADR-0057 passive capture, sourced from Gmail/Calendar. `upsertEntity`/`linkEntities` exist with **zero call sites today** — the missing code is the extractor, not a cold-start hook.
+
+7. **P4 split along the autonomy seam; P3 + P4a pulled ahead of the suppression slice.** **P4a (now):** passive-capture extraction as a standalone job over the *already-ingested* `documents` + calendar → populates the graph + first significance pass; needs neither the run-scoped autonomy override nor cold-start (the existing single user is already connected under watcher-approved autonomy). **P4b (deferred):** onboarding-time header-level seeding for *new* users, gated on the unbuilt run-scoped autonomy override (v2.1). This sequencing reverses the locked plan ordering: failure A is the user's live pain, and vertical slice 1 (Ben Book suppression) explicitly left failure A out — the per-sender suppression there is an *override on top*, not the root fix.
+
+**What this amends / builds on.**
+
+- **ADR-0050 D1** — un-defers and builds the personal-relevance primitive; the directional resolver *is* D1.
+- **ADR-0050 amendment 2026-06-10** — supersedes the "seniority is an LLM rubric judgment, not a hardcoded list" ruling: it becomes a computed graph signal; the 16a title carve-out is removed.
+- **ADR-0051** — adds `Sender relationship` to the deterministic-context layer feeding the cheap classifier (alongside sender priors + persona + observations).
+- **ADR-0057** — consumes the significance score unchanged; no contract change. Population is the passive-capture limb (P4), now split P4a/P4b.
+- **ADR-0011/0022** — reaffirms cold-start's account-holder-only scope (corrects an earlier proposal to write entities from cold-start).
+- **ADR-0055** — the rubric rewrite is eval-backed, not example-patched.
+
+**Alternatives.**
+
+- (a) **Interim rubric hardening (no graph).** Rejected: structurally can't do the directional call; another exemplar patch.
+- (b) **Global declared self-role.** Rejected: not relationship-relative; can't express direction.
+- (c) **Edge baked into the shared significance score.** Rejected: only 1 of 4 consumers needs it; breaks the scalar framing.
+- (d) **Self-entity + explicit typed `user→contact` edges from the start.** Rejected for v1: duplicates `user_facts`, adds identity-sync risk; derived direction suffices. Revisit if derived direction proves too coarse.
+- (e) **Demote the `awaiting_reply` category by significance.** Rejected: category-bend violates the honest-category principle; deprioritize within the bucket instead.
+- (f) **Cold-start writes contact entities.** Rejected: violates account-holder scope; no history to score at callback.
+- (g) **Build P4b (onboarding seeding) first.** Rejected: drags the unbuilt run-scoped autonomy override onto the critical path; P4a unblocks the actual complaint without it.
+
+**Deferred / Open.**
+
+- Significance weights/threshold — tune from data (shared with ADR-0057's open item).
+- Self-entity + typed `user→contact` edges — only if derived direction is too coarse.
+- **P4b** onboarding-time header-level seeding + the run-scoped autonomy override (v2.1).
+- Designation/org-domain as typed `entities` columns vs the `metadata` bag — decide during P4a.
+- `yourRole` resolution when the user wears multiple hats (multiple `company`/`job_title` facts).
+
+**Amendment 2026-06-16 — consumer side: the resolver emits prompt text, not a typed `{relationType, direction, theirDesignation, yourRole}` tuple.**
+
+Grilling the consumer half (the substrate — `significance.ts`, `team-graph.ts`, `entity-metadata.ts` — shipped on `codex/fix-code` unchanged) reversed micro-decision's implied output contract. In v1 three of the promised four fields are degenerate: `theirDesignation` is always `null` (no header source; P4b), there is no self-entity so `direction` has no typed edge to read, and `yourRole` is raw free-text. Shipping the literal tuple would be one real field plus three nulls/passthroughs. More importantly the consumer is the **cheap classifier's `Observations` block — text the prompt reads, not a value code branches on.** So the resolver does no typing/labelling: it renders the live signals as one observation line and lets flash-lite infer (bounded by "never infer beyond what's given").
+
+1. **No typed tuple, no `relationType` enum.** The `Sender relationship` resolver returns a rendered string folded into `assembleObservations`. Live signals, all already on the entity / in `user_facts`: the **precomputed** significance scalar (read at query time — never recomputed; `runSignificancePass` already wrote it), the reciprocity shape, the same-org-domain flag, and the user's own role. Example: `Sender relationship: weak · one-way inbound (you never replied) · not same-org · you: "Founder, Acme"`. Rejected the enum because a derived taxonomy this early ossifies a fuzzy judgment the model does better, and nothing downstream branches on it.
+2. **Scalar rendered as words, not a number.** `≥0.66 → strong`, `≥0.33 → moderate`, `>0 → weak`. The two cutoffs are the only numeric knobs and are the tunable surface (folds into ADR-0057/0059's open weights item). A model reasons better over "weak" than "0.12".
+3. **Absent row degrades to intrinsic-only.** A sender with no graph row (most senders mid-rollout) renders `Sender relationship: no prior contact on record` → 16b behaves exactly as today. Additive, safe by construction (unchanged from micro-decision 5).
+4. **Rubric flip is surgical — only the person-waiting stake is gated.** 16b's "judge stake from the email ALONE" clause is replaced: the *"a real identifiable person is waiting on you"* stake must be **corroborated by the `Sender relationship` block** — a `weak`/`no prior contact` cold inbound is not a real stakeholder however phrased; never infer a relationship beyond the block. The other intrinsic stakes (money owed/at-risk, hard deadline, lost access, a commitment to a human) are **verifiable from content regardless of sender** and stay ungated — a stranger's "invoice past due" is still a real bill. Relationship disambiguates only the human-waiting stake, which is exactly failure A.
+5. **16a founder/CEO/CTO LinkedIn carve-out deleted (confirmed).** The title-proxy was the only thing railing a cold "Founder & CEO wants to connect" request. Post-deletion a cold founder with no correspondence history → `no prior contact` → no todo; a founder the user *actually corresponds with* (`strong · two-way`) asking something → todo via the normal stake test. Intended reversal: cold inbound never rails on title alone.
+6. **Eval-gated (ADR-0055 lane).** Six evalite cases with a deterministic `todoDecision.outcome` scorer: (1) cold rec-seeker → no todo, (2) `strong · two-way` colleague ask → todo, (3) cold sender "invoice $4k past due" → todo, (4) cold founder connect → no todo, (5) `weak · one-way` + hard deadline → todo, (6) `moderate · same-org` question → todo. Cases 3 + 5 are the over-correction guardrail (intrinsic stakes survive).
+7. **Live capture folds into the daily `memory-extraction` workflow** (not triage-inline, not a new repeatable). A new **header-only** step (no LLM) reuses the recent-docs pick + `memory_extraction_status` anti-join + per-user fan-out; significance has a 90-day half-life so daily freshness is ample and per-message capture is overkill + couples graph correctness to the triage hot path. Steady-state capture **increments** per-contact correspondence counts over only newly-picked docs (`upsertEntity` is last-writes-wins on `metadata`, so overwrite would lose history beyond the window); the per-doc status row prevents double-counting. A **full** significance re-pass over all `person` entities runs at `finalize` (recency decay drifts even untouched scores; cheap in-memory). The one-off backfill script stays for the initial population.
+
+**Amendment 2026-06-16 (b) — capture hardening (code review of point 7's first cut).**
+
+The first implementation overloaded the extraction marker for capture and applied increments *after* marking, so a batched-apply failure permanently dropped a whole run's increments (mark-then-apply = at-most-once, undercount on crash). Two fixes:
+
+8. **Capture has its own marker, and increments commit atomically with it.** New nullable column `memory_extraction_status.captured_into_graph_at` (migration `0038`) — distinct from `last_extracted_at` (LLM facts ≠ header capture). The `process` step reads which of the batch's docs are already stamped, accumulates only the rest, then folds the increments **and** stamps those docs in **one transaction** (`applyCorrespondenceIncrements(…, tx)` + the `UPDATE`). A failed apply rolls the stamp back too, so the next run retries — **at-least-once, never double-counted**, honoring point 7's idempotency intent without the silent-drop window. Zero-yield docs (all-service senders) are still stamped so they aren't rescanned. Backfill is unaffected (no `tx` → its prior per-write behavior). Scoped to the incremental path: the pre-existing backfill↔incremental double-count seam (docs ingested-but-unextracted at backfill time) stays tolerated under decay; the column is the seam to close later if it ever matters.
+9. **People are upserted by EMAIL ALIAS, not canonical name.** `upsertEntity` keys on `(user, kind, canonical_name)`, so a new contact whose display name collides with a *different* existing person merged onto that row and clobbered their correspondence. New `upsertPersonByAlias` matches by alias (the stable identity for a person), preserves the existing row's canonical name, and merges metadata last-writes-wins (so the significance pass's score survives a capture write). `persistContacts` uses it on both the merge and overwrite paths, dropping the separate alias `SELECT` it previously did per contact.
